  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <main class="docs-content">

    <!-- INTRODUCTION -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="intro">
      <h2><i data-lucide="zap" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Getting Started</h2>
      <p>
        Welcome to PracticeAPI! This is a free REST API designed for developers to practice building applications, test API calls, and learn how real-world APIs work. No authentication required — just start making requests.
      </p>
      <p>
        PracticeAPI provides realistic, structured JSON data across 20+ categories including users, locations, finance data, products, and much more.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- BASE URL -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="baseurl">
      <h2><i data-lucide="link" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Base URL</h2>
      <p>All API requests use the following base URL:</p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header">Base URL</div>
        <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
        <pre>https://practiceapi.up.railway.app/api/v1</pre>
      </div>
      <p>Append the desired endpoint to this base URL to make requests.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- AUTHENTICATION -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="auth">
      <h2><i data-lucide="lock" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Authentication</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>No authentication required!</strong> PracticeAPI is completely open and free to use. You don't need to provide API keys, tokens, or credentials. Just make requests directly to the endpoints.
      </p>
      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> This is perfect for learning and testing. In production APIs, you'll typically need authentication headers like <code>Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN</code>.
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- MAKING REQUESTS -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="making-requests">
      <h2><i data-lucide="send" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Making Requests</h2>
      
      <h3>HTTP Methods</h3>
      <p>PracticeAPI supports all standard HTTP methods:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><span class="method GET">GET</span> - Retrieve data</li>
        <li><span class="method POST">POST</span> - Create new data</li>
        <li><span class="method PUT">PUT</span> - Update existing data</li>
        <li><span class="method DELETE">DELETE</span> - Delete data</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Request Headers</h3>
      <p>When sending data, include the proper content type:</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Header</th>
            <th>Value</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>Content-Type</code></td>
            <td><code>application/json</code></td>
            <td>For JSON data in POST/PUT requests</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>Accept</code></td>
            <td><code>application/json</code></td>
            <td>Request JSON response format</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Query Parameters</h3>
      <p>Most endpoints support query parameters for filtering and pagination:</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Parameter</th>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>limit</code></td>
            <td>Number</td>
            <td>Limit number of results returned (default: 10, max: 100)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>skip</code></td>
            <td>Number</td>
            <td>Skip first N results for pagination</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>sort</code></td>
            <td>String</td>
            <td>Sort results (ascending: field, descending: -field)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>📝 Example:</strong> <code>GET /api/v1/person?limit=5&skip=0&sort=-createdAt</code>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RESPONSES -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="responses">
      <h2><i data-lucide="check-circle" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Responses</h2>
      
      <h3>Success Response (200 OK)</h3>
      <p>Successful requests return a 200 status code with data:</p>
      <div class="response-example">
        <div class="response-label">Response Format</div>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">JSON</div>
          <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
          <pre>{
  <span class="str">"success"</span>: <span class="kw">true</span>,
  <span class="str">"status"</span>: <span class="num">200</span>,
  <span class="str">"data"</span>: {
    <span class="str">"id"</span>: <span class="str">"abc123"</span>,
    <span class="str">"name"</span>: <span class="str">"John Doe"</span>,
    <span class="str">"email"</span>: <span class="str">"john@example.com"</span>
  },
  <span class="str">"message"</span>: <span class="str">"Data retrieved successfully"</span>
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Paginated Response</h3>
      <p>Endpoints that return multiple items include pagination info:</p>
      <div class="response-example">
        <div class="response-label">Pagination Format</div>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">JSON</div>
          <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
          <pre>{
  <span class="str">"success"</span>: <span class="kw">true</span>,
  <span class="str">"status"</span>: <span class="num">200</span>,
  <span class="str">"dataset"</span>: <span class="str">"person"</span>,
  <span class="str">"data"</span>: [
    { <span class="str">"id"</span>: <span class="str">"1"</span>, <span class="str">"name"</span>: <span class="str">"John Doe"</span>, <span class="str">"email"</span>: <span class="str">"john@example.com"</span> },
    { <span class="str">"id"</span>: <span class="str">"2"</span>, <span class="str">"name"</span>: <span class="str">"Jane Smith"</span>, <span class="str">"email"</span>: <span class="str">"jane@example.com"</span> }
  ],
  <span class="str">"pagination"</span>: {
    <span class="str">"totalCount"</span>: <span class="num">100</span>,
    <span class="str">"limit"</span>: <span class="num">10</span>,
    <span class="str">"skip"</span>: <span class="num">0</span>,
    <span class="str">"totalPages"</span>: <span class="num">10</span>,
    <span class="str">"currentPage"</span>: <span class="num">1</span>
  },
  <span class="str">"message"</span>: <span class="str">"Retrieved 2 records from person"</span>
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ALL ENDPOINTS -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="endpoints">
      <h2><i data-lucide="layers" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> All Endpoints</h2>
      <p>PracticeAPI provides 20+ data categories. Here are the main endpoints:</p>

      <h3>Categories & Endpoints</h3>
      <table>
