      <h3>POST Request - Create Data</h3>
      <p>Creating new data with POST request:</p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header">JavaScript</div>
        <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
        <pre><span class="kw">async function</span> <span class="fn">createPerson</span>() {
  <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">data</span> = {
    <span class="str">name</span>: <span class="str">'John Doe'</span>,
    <span class="str">email</span>: <span class="str">'john@example.com'</span>,
    <span class="str">age</span>: <span class="num">25</span>
  };

  <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">response</span> = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">fetch</span>(<span class="str">'https://practiceapi.up.railway.app/api/v1/person'</span>, {
    <span class="str">method</span>: <span class="str">'POST'</span>,
    <span class="str">headers</span>: { <span class="str">'Content-Type'</span>: <span class="str">'application/json'</span> },
    <span class="str">body</span>: <span class="fn">JSON</span>.<span class="fn">stringify</span>(<span class="fn">data</span>)
  });

  <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">result</span> = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">response</span>.<span class="fn">json</span>();
  <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="fn">result</span>);
}</pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Pagination with Sorting</h3>
      <p>Fetch paginated data with custom sorting:</p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header">JavaScript</div>
        <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
        <pre><span class="kw">async function</span> <span class="fn">fetchPaginatedData</span>() {
  <span class="key">const</span> page = <span class="num">1</span>;
  <span class="key">const</span> pageSize = <span class="num">10</span>;
  <span class="key">const</span> skip = (page - <span class="num">1</span>) * pageSize;

  <span class="key">const</span> url = <span class="kw">new</span> <span class="fn">URL</span>(<span class="str">'https://practiceapi.up.railway.app/api/v1/person'</span>);
  url.<span class="fn">searchParams</span>.<span class="fn">append</span>(<span class="str">'limit'</span>, pageSize);
  url.<span class="fn">searchParams</span>.<span class="fn">append</span>(<span class="str">'skip'</span>, skip);
  url.<span class="fn">searchParams</span>.<span class="fn">append</span>(<span class="str">'sort'</span>, <span class="str">'-createdAt'</span>);

  <span class="kw">try</span> {
    <span class="key">const</span> response = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">fetch</span>(url);
    <span class="key">const</span> result = <span class="kw">await</span> response.<span class="fn">json</span>();

    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'Data:'</span>, result.data);
    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'Current Page:'</span>, result.pagination.currentPage);
    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'Total Pages:'</span>, result.pagination.totalPages);
  } <span class="kw">catch</span> (error) {
    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">error</span>(<span class="str">'Error:'</span>, error);
  }
}</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ERROR HANDLING -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="errors">
      <h2><i data-lucide="alert-circle" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Error Handling</h2>
      
      <h3>HTTP Status Codes</h3>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Status</th>
            <th>Meaning</th>
            <th>Example</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>200</code></td>
            <td>OK - Request successful</td>
            <td>Data retrieved successfully</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>201</code></td>
            <td>Created - Resource created</td>
            <td>New data created</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>400</code></td>
            <td>Bad Request - Invalid parameters</td>
            <td>Invalid query parameters</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>404</code></td>
            <td>Not Found - Resource doesn't exist</td>
            <td>Invalid endpoint</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>500</code></td>
            <td>Server Error - Internal error</td>
            <td>Unexpected server error</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Error Response Format</h3>
      <p>When an error occurs, you'll receive a response like this:</p>
      <div class="response-example">
        <div class="response-label">Error Response</div>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">JSON</div>
          <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
          <pre>{
  <span class="str">"success"</span>: <span class="kw">false</span>,
  <span class="str">"status"</span>: <span class="num">400</span>,
  <span class="str">"message"</span>: <span class="str">"Invalid request parameters"</span>,
  <span class="str">"error"</span>: {
    <span class="str">"code"</span>: <span class="str">"INVALID_PARAM"</span>,
    <span class="str">"details"</span>: <span class="str">"limit must be a number"</span>
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Handling Errors in Code</h3>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-header">JavaScript</div>
        <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
        <pre><span class="kw">async function</span> <span class="fn">fetchData</span>() {
  <span class="kw">try</span> {
    <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">response</span> = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">fetch</span>(<span class="str">'https://practiceapi.up.railway.app/api/v1/person'</span>);
    
    <span class="kw">if</span> (!<span class="fn">response</span>.<span class="fn">ok</span>) {
      <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">error</span> = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">response</span>.<span class="fn">json</span>();
      <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">error</span>(<span class="str">'API Error:'</span>, <span class="fn">error</span>.<span class="fn">message</span>);
      <span class="kw">return</span>;
    }
    
    <span class="key">const</span> <span class="fn">data</span> = <span class="kw">await</span> <span class="fn">response</span>.<span class="fn">json</span>();
    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">log</span>(<span class="str">'Success:'</span>, <span class="fn">data</span>);
  } <span class="kw">catch</span> (<span class="fn">error</span>) {
    <span class="fn">console</span>.<span class="fn">error</span>(<span class="str">'Network Error:'</span>, <span class="fn">error</span>);
  }
}</pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RATE LIMITING -->
    <section class="doc-section" id="ratelimit">
      <h2><i data-lucide="zap" style="width: 28px; margin-right: 8px; vertical-align: -2px;"></i> Rate Limiting</h2>
      
      <h3>Limits</h3>
      <p>PracticeAPI implements rate limiting to ensure fair usage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>100 requests per 15 minutes</strong> per IP address</li>
        <li>Applies to all API endpoints</li>
        <li>Resets automatically after the 15-minute window</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Rate Limit Headers</h3>
      <p>Each response includes rate limit information in the headers:</p>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Header</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code></td>
            <td>Total requests allowed in window (100)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code></td>
            <td>Requests remaining in current window</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code></td>
            <td>Unix timestamp when limit resets</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h3>Exceeded Rate Limit</h3>
      <p>When you exceed the rate limit, you'll receive a 429 response:</p>
      <div class="response-example">
        <div class="response-label">Rate Limit Exceeded</div>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">JSON</div>
          <button class="copy-code-btn"><i data-lucide="copy" style="width:14px;height:14px;"></i> Copy</button>
          <pre>{
  <span class="str">"error"</span>: <span class="str">"Too many requests, please try again later."</span>
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="info-box">
        <strong>💡 Tip:</strong> Check the <code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code> header to monitor your usage and avoid hitting the limit.
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

